Entries.default: "Should we be concerned about that?"
"I thought the volcanoes in these parts were dormant?"
"Is that... do these places always make such a fearful noise?"
"The volcano rolls in slumber, I say. We should not be here."
"Ain't the volcanoes in Magran's Teeth supposed to be inactive? I got a bad feeling this one's waking up..."
"This does not sound good..."
"All right, that one felt more serious."
"That one felt stronger than the first."
"Ship shakes like this, it be past time to abandon it."
"I'm thinking this place ain't going to hold up much longer. What say we hurry, Watcher?"
"We should move quickly..."
"Too late to turn around, captain?"
"I do not know much about volcanoes, but when they keep rumbling like this, that is not good, yes?"
"Fantastic, cap. Fucking fantastic. Don't suppose there be another entrance."
"Supposing this volcano blows, what're the odds any of us but Gaun survives it?"
"Shouldn't they be leaving, too?"
"Ishi, I don't want you playing with those big birds."
"I hope they do not dine on fish."
"Careful! All this rumbling's riling the critters up good!"
"I don't like this, captain."
"It is not just the mountain that awakens... we disturb the fires of Magran herself."
"We stare down the open jaws of Tangaloa. Captain, it has been... an honor."
